('spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors:mcq:03813483', 'spanish', 'spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors', 'G.6 Pronouns, Negatives and Connectors', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘La chica ___ vive al lado es mi vecina.’ (who/that)", "options": ["que", "quien", "lo que", "cual"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘que’ links a noun (la chica) to extra information. ‘quien’ needs a preposition, ‘lo que’ refers to an idea, and ‘cual’ needs an article."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors:mcq:494cfa03', 'spanish', 'spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors', 'G.6 Pronouns, Negatives and Connectors', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "How do you say ‘There is nobody here’?", "options": ["No hay nadie aquí.", "Hay nadie aquí.", "No hay alguien aquí.", "No hay nada aquí."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘No hay nadie aquí’ needs the double negative. B drops ‘no’; C wrongly pairs ‘no’ with ‘alguien’ (someone); D confuses nadie (nobody) with nada (nothing)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors:mcq:6547721a', 'spanish', 'spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors', 'G.6 Pronouns, Negatives and Connectors', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘No voy a la fiesta ___ tengo mucha tarea.’ (because)", "options": ["porque", "aunque", "pero", "también"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘porque’ gives the reason. ‘aunque’ (although) reverses the logic, ‘pero’ (but) and ‘también’ (also) don''t fit a cause."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors:mcq:e0d2dd64', 'spanish', 'spanish:g-6-pronouns-negatives-and-connectors', 'G.6 Pronouns, Negatives and Connectors', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which best translates ‘un poco cansado’?", "options": ["a bit tired", "extremely tired", "never tired", "the most tired of all"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘un poco’ softens the adjective to ‘a bit’. The distractors overstate it, negate it, or turn it into a superlative."}'::jsonb),
